; Bombs are complicated. They have zero move cost to load, which is necessary to allow them to load up and be used
; on the turn they're created. They have a double move cost for unload, which evens it out to prevent double-hauling
; them across the planet for a distant bombing mission. PROBLEM IS: "Transport Board" allows loading while already
; transported in the other actionenablers. And we don't want it to or it would be nightmare micromanaged
; deboard-first-now-board extra keystrokes all over the place and a rethinking of all our move costs for such things.
; However, for Bombs only, by charging nothing to board, double-charging deboarding, and disallowing boarding while
; transported, everything works out peachy. You can double-haul any bomb but not use it this turn. You can single-haul
; a conventional bomb and use it this turn (with no tired attack because conv.Bombs don't have it), you can single-haul a
; nuclear bomb and use it this turn. You can load either, on the turn it's made, onto a Bomber and be ready for action
; at full moves.
[actionenabler_board_bombs]
action        = "Transport Board"
actor_reqs    =
    { "type",          "name",          "range", "present"
      "UnitClassFlag", "TerrainSpeed",  "Local", FALSE  ;not Land
      "UnitClassFlag", "WaterVessel",   "Local", FALSE  ;not Sea
