;NOTE the two enablers below SHOULD be fixed by 17Jan2023 commit "Fix units with (moves_left â‰¤ 1) can't EMBARK" ********************************************************************************** NOTE: DELETE THESE
;Thus we can schedule them for deletion, but leaving them would allow units stranded for any other reason to  ************************************************************************************ NOTE: DELETE THESE
;always be able to board to save themselves from drowning.
;
;The two enablers below catch a bug in complex rulesets that have complex Boarding rules.
;The bug is that a unit doing order_move or order_perform_action "transport embark" to a
;transport on a non-native tile, are allowed to move to that tile because embark is legal.
;But then the movepoints are subtracted first, and then because it has no moves left, it
;no longer fulfills the legality for Embark action, leaving it stranded on the water.
;The logic then seems to fall thru to check if "Transport Board" would be legal and it
;tries that next, but if the ruleset has complex rules for "Transport Board" and that's also
;no longer legal, the unit can't board in order to pull off the verisimilitude of doing
;an embark. Apparently it assumed or was only tested with rulesets with legacy rules
;of zero moves_left being allowed for Boarding. Ideally we'd debug this logic on the
;server to see where it's slipping over itself and ALLOWING the move BECAUSE
;embark is legal then NOT allowing the embarcation to actually happen because it does
;the move, loses move points, then lost the legality to embark/board and becomes
;stranded in the water. For now, we are making two ruleset enablers to allow faulty
;server logic to work, where a unit that would obviously be stranded in the water
;is allowed to perform the server's fallthru logic of doing a Boarding action.
;This also allows any other bugged units floating in water to Board and get picked
;up by ships coming by, should that ever happen for other reasons.
[actionenabler_embark_fall_thru_bug_fix_1]             ; BUG FIX for land units who aren't LandRoad units
action        = "Transport Board"
actor_reqs    =
    { "type",         "name",           "range", "present"
      "MinMoveFrags", "1",              "Local", FALSE  ;only catch bugged units stranded with ZERO MOVES as non-passengers on unlivable tiles
